    "summary": "I am a professional Engineer with ten years of Chemical plant operations experience . I am driven by continuous improvement and enjoy the diversity and complexities experienced when designing and implementing projects.\n\nSpecialties: \nRoot Cause Analysis (RCA), Management of Change (MOC), Continuous Improvement, Project development, Leading process deviation investigations, OEE.\nPastillation and packaging, Distillation, Batch reactor operation, Solids handling and transport, Refrigeration and liquefaction.\n\nSynthomer Chemicals, Netherlands\nProcess Improvement Engineer\nLeading the Process Improvement initiative for my appointed area I evaluate new opportunities through a data driven approach, take ownership of MOC\u2019s, Drive the implementation of solutions and support operations with investigations more advanced analysis is needed. \n\nSTAR Group, Netherlands\nProcess Engineer: Process design and Production support\nI have developed several Process design packages for essential plant improvements and am currently fulfilling a temporary assignment, leading a team of experts to improve packaging line reliability.\n\nSasol, RSA\nProcess Engineer: Phenolics value chain\nAs the value chain lead engineer I supported the production engineering team technically, coordinated feed volume and product quality as well as managing the continuous improvement initiatives portfolio to enhance product value.\n\nProcess Engineer: Vinyls operations\nDaily operations monitoring and support to enhance production volume and quality.\nDevelop and Initiate modifications and capital projects\nSupport the MOC process and project life cycle through feasibility, design, safe implementation and commissioning.\nLeading incident investigations to root causes and defining corrective actions.\n\nMasters degree in Gasification reaction kinetics\nChartered Member \u2013 MIChemE (99963066)",
